The KwaZulu-Natal government will be writing to the president, asking for a special official funeral to honour late Ladysmith Black Mambazo founder Joseph Shabalala. Courtesy #DStv403 LADYSMITH - The KwaZulu-Natal government will be writing to President Cyril Ramaphosa to ask for a special official funeral to honour late Ladysmith Black Mambazo founder, Joseph Shabalala. He died on Tuesday morning in a Pretoria hospital. READ: Joseph Shabalala's family announces date for funeral Tributes continue to pour in for the internationally-renowned music maestro. The provincial government says Shabalala is a legend who should be given a befitting send-off. READ: Remembering Ladysmith Black Mambazo founder Joseph Shabalala "As the provincial government, we will now start with plans to engage the President, write to him and ask that Shabalala be honoured with a special funeral because the whole world will be watching his funeral," said KZN Arts and Culture MEC Hlengiwe Mavimbela. Shabalala will be laid to rest on 22 February in Ladysmith.